{"id":"mai-y3zw","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"P0: Support priority updates via CLI","tags":["p0","core","ramboard"],"body":"## P0: Support priority updates via CLI\n\n### Problem\n\nNo `mai priority` command exists. The engine's fold logic already handles `field priority` events via `applyFieldChange`, but there's no CLI command to emit one. Ramboard's ticket-writer logs a warning and skips priority updates.\n\n### Context\n\nDiscovered during ramboard→maitake rewiring. Status, tags, and assignee all have CLI commands. Priority doesn't.\n\n### CLI addition\n\n```bash\nmai priority \u003cid\u003e \u003cN\u003e    # N = 0-4\n```\n\nEmits:\n```\nkind event\nedge updates note:\u003cid\u003e\nfield priority\nvalue \u003cN\u003e\n```\n\n### Engine\n\nFold already works — `applyFieldChange` has `case \"priority\"`. Just needs the CLI wiring.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `mai priority \u003cid\u003e 1` creates a priority event\n- [ ] `mai --json show \u003cid\u003e` reflects new priority after fold\n- [ ] `mai --json ls` shows updated priority in summary\n\n### Depends on\n\nNothing — fold logic exists, just missing the command.","timestamp":"2026-03-28T21:27:45Z","branch":"main"}

